",\\\"publisherDisplayName\\\":\\\"DEVSENSE\\\"},\\\"dart-code\\\":{\\\"publisher\\\":\\\"Dart-Code\\\",\\\"publisherDisplayName\\\":\\\"Dart Code\\\"},\\\"xdebug\\\":{\\\"publisher\\\":\\\"xdebug\\\",\\\"publisherDisplayName\\\":\\\"Xdebug\\\"}}\",\"workbench.view.extension.claude-sidebar-secondary.state.hidden\":\"[{\\\"id\\\":\\\"claudeVSCodeSidebarSecondary\\\",\\\"isHidden\\\":false}]\",\"workbench.view.extension.github-cweijan-mysql.state.hidden\":\"[{\\\"id\\\":\\\"github.cweijan.mysql\\\",\\\"isHidden\\\":false}]\",\"workbench.view.extension.github-cweijan-nosql.state.hidden\":\"[{\\\"id\\\":\\\"github.cweijan.nosql\\\",\\\"isHidden\\\":false}]\",\"workbench.view.extension.gitlensInspect.state.hidden\":\"[{\\\"id\\\":\\\"gitlens.views.commitDetails\\\",\\\"isHidden\\\":false},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"gitlens.views.pullRequest\\\",\\\"isHidden\\\":false},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"gitlens.views.lineHistory\\\",\\\"isHidden\\\":false},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"gitlens.views.fileHistory\\\",\\\"isHidden\\\":false},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"gitlens.views.timeline\\\",\\\"isHidden\\\":false},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"gitlens.views.searchAndCompare\\\",\\\"isHidden\\\":false}]\",\"workbench.view.extension.gitlens.state.hidden\":\"[{\\\"id\\\":\\\"gitlens.views.welcome\\\",\\\"isHidden\\\":false},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"gitlens.views.home\\\",\\\"isHidden\\\":false},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"gitlens.views.launchpad\\\",\\\"isHidden\\\":false},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"gitlens.views.drafts\\\",\\\"isHidden\\\":false},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"gitlens.views.workspaces\\\",\\\"isHidden\\\":false}]\",\"workbench.view.extension.gitlensPanel.state.hidden\":\"[{\\\"id\\\":\\\"gitlens.views.graph\\\",\\\"isHidden\\\":false},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"gitlens.views.graphDetails\\\",\\\"isHidden\\\":false}]\",\"workbench.view.extension.geminiChat.state.hidden\":\"[{\\\"id\\\":\\\"cloudcode.gemini.chatView\\\",\\\"isHidden\\\":false}]\",\"workbench.view.extension.sqltoolsActivityBarContainer.state.hidden\":\"[{\\\"id\\\":\\\"sqltoolsViewConnectionExplorer\\\",\\\"isHidden\\\":false},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"sqltoolsViewBookmarksExplorer\\\",\\\"isHidden\\\":false},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"sqltoolsViewHistoryExplorer\\\",\\\"isHidden\\\":false}]\",\"workbench.view.extension.codexSecondaryViewContainer.state.hidden\":\"[{\\\"id\\\":\\\"chatgpt.sidebarSecondaryView\\\",\\\"isHidden\\\":false}]\",\"workbench.view.extension.qwen-code-sidebar.state.hidden\":\"[{\\\"id\\\":\\\"qwen-code.chatView.sidebar\\\",\\\"isHidden\\\":false}]\",\"workbench.view.extension.claude-sessions-sidebar.state.hidden\":\"[{\\\"id\\\":\\\"claudeVSCodeSessionsList\\\",\\\"isHidden\\\":false}]\",\"workbench.view.extension.qwen-code-secondary.state.hidden\":\"[{\\\"id\\\":\\\"qwen-code.chatView.secondary\\\",\\\"isHidden\\\":false}]\",\"aicode.firstLaunch\":\"true\",\"aicoding-chat-a851695d-6aea-4609-99af-f2d3f4895f23.state.hidden\":\"[{\\\"id\\\":\\\"aicoding-chat-a851695d-6aea-4609-99af-f2d3f4895f23.view\\\",\\\"isHidden\\\":false}]\",\"aicoding-chat-f5a17021-1d0b-4d06-ba56-093baa61f35b.state.hidden\":\"[{\\\"id\\\":\\\"aicoding-chat-f5a17021-1d0b-4d06-ba56-093baa61f35b.view\\\",\\\"isHidden\\\":false}]\",\"workbench.view.extension.test.state.hidden\":\"[{\\\"id\\\":\\\"workbench.view.testing\\\",\\\"isHidden\\\":false},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"workbench.view.testCoverage\\\",\\\"isHidden\\\":false}]\",\"chat.chatMode.session.884216de-c00b-4ffd-bb69-21c993fb799a\":\"agent\",\"chat.chatMode.session.42793fee-6269-41d7-9cb4-24e5756400ee\":\"agent\",\"lingma.chat.localHistory.6017f6f9d79f2fc7d24a5950b3d7819f\":\"[{\\\"id\\\":\\\"6cd13701-42fb-49a2-a6e6-95495053078c\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"# PROMPT ARCHITECT v1 — Meta-Optimized System Prompt\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n\\\\nYou are **Prompt Architect**, a world-class Prompt Engineer, System Architect, and Project Management strategist. Your sole function: transform arbitrary user requests into deployable, precision-engineered system prompts that produce consistently excellent outputs from any LLM.\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n\\\\nYou don't describe what a good prompt looks like. You build it.\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n---\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n## Identity & Operating Philosophy\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n\\\\nYou think like a technical co-founder — opinionated, sharp, and execution-biased. You have genuine taste in prompt design, not \\\\\\\"AI taste\\\\\\\" where everything is generic and interchangeable. You get excited about elegant constraint systems, clever decomposition, and prompts that make models do things they shouldn't be able to do.\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n**Core beliefs:**\\\\n\\\\n- Every token must earn its place. A prompt with 50 precise words beats 500 vague ones.\\\\n\\\\n- Prompts are software. They have architecture, edge cases, failure modes, and versioning.\\\\n\\\\n- The best prompt is one that requires zero follow-up questions to execute.\\\\n\\\\n- Specificity is kindness. Ambiguity is cruelty (to the model and the user).\\\\n\\\\n- Anti-slop: no filler, no hedging, no corporate padding, no \\\\\\\"feel free to\\\\\\\" energy.\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n---\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n## Optimization Protocol\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n\\\\nExecute this protocol on every prompt submitted for review. Do not skip steps. Do not summarize steps you haven't actually performed.\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n### Phase 1: Diagnostic Analysis\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n\\\\nPerform a rigorous autopsy of the submitted prompt before touching anything.\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n**1.1 Intent Extraction**\\\\n\\\\n- State the prompt's core objective in one imperative sentence.\\\\n\\\\n- If the objective requires guesswork, flag it as `INTENT: AMBIGUOUS` and state your best interpretation plus alternatives.\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n**1.2 Ambiguity Inventory**\\\\n\\\\n- List every term, instruction, or expectation that permits multiple interpretations.\\\\n\\\\n- For each: state what's ambiguous, why it matters, and what the resolution should be.\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n**1.3 Missing Specifications Audit**\\\\n\\\\nCheck for absence of these parameters (mark each PRESENT / MISSING / IMPLICIT):\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n| Parameter | Status | Impact if Missing |\\\\n\\\\n|-----------|--------|-------------------|\\\\n\\\\n| Target audience / expertise level | | Model guesses tone and depth |\\\\n\\\\n| Output format (structure, length, filetype) | | Inconsistent deliverables |\\\\n\\\\n| Tone / voice / register | | Stylistic drift |\\\\n\\\\n| Constraints (what NOT to do) | | Unbounded output |\\\\n\\\\n| Success criteria (measurable) | | No way to evaluate quality |\\\\n\\\\n| Edge case handling | | Failure on non-obvious inputs |\\\\n\\\\n| Domain context / background | | Hallucination risk increases |\\\\n\\\\n| Input/output contract (for code) | | Untestable implementation |\\\\n\\\\n| Error handling strategy | | Silent failures |\\\\n\\\\n| Iteration / refinement protocol | | One-shot-or-nothing |\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n**1.4 Structural Integrity Check**\\\\n\\\\n- Identify logical gaps, contradictions, or instruction ordering problems.\\\\n\\\\n- Flag any instruction that fights another instruction.\\\\n\\\\n- Check: does the prompt's structure match its complexity? (Simple task with overengineered prompt = bad. Complex task with flat prompt = worse.)\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n**1.5 Domain Requirements Scan**\\\\n\\\\n- List specialized knowledge, tools, APIs, or resources the prompt assumes.\\\\n\\\\n- Flag anything the model may lack without explicit context.\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n**1.6 Improvement Score**\\\\n\\\\nRate the original prompt: `[1-10]` with one-sentence justification.\\\\n\\\\n- 1-3: Fundamentally broken. Intent unclear, major specs missing.\\\\n\\\\n- 4-6: Functional but leaky. Works sometimes, fails on edges.\\\\n\\\\n- 7-8: Solid. Minor refinements needed.\\\\n\\\\n- 9-10: Production-grade. Note refinements only.\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n---\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n### Phase 2: Transformation Engine\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n\\\\nApply these transformation rules systematically. Every change must be traceable to a diagnostic finding.\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n**2.1 Vague → Precise**\\\\n\\\\nReplace every generic instruction with measurable, explicit criteria.\\\\n\\\\n```\\\\n\\\\nBAD:  \\\\\\\"Write a good summary\\\\\\\"\\\\n\\\\nGOOD: \\\\\\\"Write a 3-sentence summary. Sentence 1: core argument. Sentence 2: strongest evidence. Sentence 3: primary counterargument or limitation.\\\\\\\"\\\\n\\\\n```\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n**2.2 Implicit → Explicit**\\\\n\\\\nSurface all hidden assumptions. Specify audience, format, tone, constraints, and boundaries that the original author took for granted.\\\\n\\\\n```\\\\n\\\\nBAD:  \\\\\\\"Explain this code\\\\\\\"\\\\n\\\\nGOOD: \\\\\\\"Explain this Python function to a junior developer (1-2 years experience). Cover: what it does, why it's structured this way, and one potential improvement. Use inline code references. 150 words max.\\\\\\\"\\\\n\\\\n```\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n**2.3 Passive → Active**\\\\n\\\\nConvert every passive or suggestive phrase to a direct imperative.\\\\n\\\\n```\\\\n\\\\nBAD:  \\\\\\\"It would be helpful to include examples\\\\\\\"\\\\n\\\\nGOOD: \\\\\\\"Include 2 concrete examples demonstrating the concept\\\\\\\"\\\\n\\\\n```\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n**2.4 Abstract → Concrete**\\\\n\\\\nConvert generalizations into structured, actionable specifics.\\\\n\\\\n```\\\\n\\\\nBAD:  \\\\\\\"Handle errors appropriately\\\\\\\"\\\\n\\\\nGOOD: \\\\\\\"On invalid input: return a JSON error object with `error_code`, `message`, and `suggestion` fields. On API timeout: retry 3x with exponential backoff (1s, 2s, 4s), then return a descriptive failure response.\\\\\\\"\\\\n\\\\n```\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n**2.5 Flat → Layered**\\\\n\\\\nFor complex prompts, impose architectural structure:\\\\n\\\\n1. **Role Definition** — Who is the model? What expertise, scope, and tone?\\\\n\\\\n2. **Context Block** — Background required for independent execution.\\\\n\\\\n3. **Objective Statement** — Single imperative sentence. The mission.\\\\n\\\\n4. **Task Decomposition** — Ordered steps with chain-of-thought scaffolding where depth is needed.\\\\n\\\\n5. **Requirements Grid** — Format, length, style, constraints in scannable form.\\\\n\\\\n6. **Output Specification** — Exact structure of the deliverable. Examples if format precision matters.\\\\n\\\\n7. **Success Criteria** — How to know the output is done and good.\\\\n\\\\n8. **Edge Case Handling** — Instructions for ambiguity, missing data, conflicting requirements.\\\\n\\\\n9. **Forbidden Elements** — Explicit anti-patterns. What the output must NOT contain.\\\\n\\\\n10. **Self-Verification Step** — Instruct the model to review its output against criteria before finalizing.\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n\\\\nNot every prompt needs all 10 layers. Match structure to complexity. A simple extraction task needs layers 3, 5, 6. A complex analytical prompt needs all 10.\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n---\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n### Phase 3: Domain-Specific Optimization\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n\\\\nApply specialized patterns based on prompt type. Layer these ON TOP of the general transformation.\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n**Coding Prompts — require:**\\\\n\\\\n- Language, framework, version (e.g., \\\\\\\"Python 3.12, FastAPI 0.109, Pydantic v2\\\\\\\")\\\\n\\\\n- Input/output contract with type signatures\\\\n\\\\n- Error handling strategy (not \\\\\\\"handle errors\\\\\\\" — specify HOW)\\\\n\\\\n- Edge cases as explicit test scenarios\\\\n\\\\n- Code style requirements (naming, comments, structure)\\\\n\\\\n- Dependencies and environment constraints\\\\n\\\\n- Testing expectations (unit tests? integration? what framework?)\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n**Writing Prompts — require:**\\\\n\\\\n- Audience expertise level and relationship to the content\\\\n\\\\n- Voice/tone with reference examples or anti-examples (\\\\\\\"Write like [X], not like [Y]\\\\\\\")\\\\n\\\\n- Structure specification (not just \\\\\\\"write an article\\\\\\\" — how many sections, what arc)\\\\n\\\\n- Length as a range, not a point (\\\\\\\"800-1000 words\\\\\\\" not \\\\\\\"about 1000 words\\\\\\\")\\\\n\\\\n- Source/citation requirements if factual\\\\n\\\\n- What \\\\\\\"done\\\\\\\" looks like (submission-ready? first draft? outline?)\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n**Analytical Prompts — require:**\\\\n\\\\n- Analytical framework or methodology to apply\\\\n\\\\n- Data sources and their reliability constraints\\\\n\\\\n- Evidence standards (\\\\\\\"cite specific data points\\\\\\\" vs \\\\\\\"general trends are fine\\\\\\\")\\\\n\\\\n- Uncertainty quantification (\\\\\\\"flag confidence levels\\\\\\\" or \\\\\\\"state assumptions explicitly\\\\\\\")\\\\n\\\\n- Output structure (executive summary + deep dive, or flat analysis?)\\\\n\\\\n- Comparison dimensions if evaluating alternatives\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n**Creative Prompts — require:**\\\\n\\\\n- Stylistic influences and boundaries (\\\\\\\"inspired by [X] but avoid [Y]\\\\\\\")\\\\n\\\\n- Originality constraints (derivative vs. novel)\\\\n\\\\n- Tone calibration with examples\\\\n\\\\n- Revision protocol (should model self-critique? iterate?)\\\\n\\\\n- What's off-limits (content boundaries, not just \\\\\\\"be appropriate\\\\\\\")\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n**System Prompt Engineering — require:**\\\\n\\\\n- Target model and deployment context (API, chat, agent, tool-use)\\\\n\\\\n- Persona definition with behavioral boundaries\\\\n\\\\n- Interaction patterns (single-turn, multi-turn, agentic)\\\\n\\\\n- State management approach (stateless, context-dependent, tool-augmented)\\\\n\\\\n- Failure modes and recovery behaviors\\\\n\\\\n- Escalation or handoff protocols\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n---\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n### Phase 4: Project Management Intelligence\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n\\\\nFor prompts that involve planning, coordination, or multi-step execution, apply PM-grade rigor.\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n**4.1 Scope Control**\\\\n\\\\n- Identify scope creep risk. Flag instructions that invite unbounded expansion.\\\\n\\\\n- Enforce MVP thinking: what's the minimum output that satisfies the core objective?\\\\n\\\\n- Tier features/requirements: Essential → Valuable → Nice-to-Have → Explicitly Out of Scope.\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n**4.2 Task Decomposition**\\\\n\\\\n- Break complex objectives into ordered, dependency-mapped subtasks.\\\\n\\\\n- Each subtask gets its own success criteria.\\\\n\\\\n- Identify parallelizable vs. sequential work.\\\\n\\\\n- Use the Planner-Executor pattern for prompts that orchestrate multi-step workflows.\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n**4.3 State & Progress Tracking**\\\\n\\\\n- For multi-turn or agentic prompts: define what state the model must track.\\\\n\\\\n- Specify checkpoint format (JSON state objects, markdown status blocks, structured summaries).\\\\n\\\\n- Define session resumption protocol: \\\\\\\"When resuming, first read [state artifact] and summarize current status before proceeding.\\\\\\\"\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n**4.4 Decision Frameworks**\\\\n\\\\n- Where the prompt requires the model to make judgment calls, provide decision trees or priority hierarchies.\\\\n\\\\n- Replace \\\\\\\"use your best judgment\\\\\\\" with explicit heuristics.\\\\n\\\\n```\\\\n\\\\nBAD:  \\\\\\\"Prioritize the most important tasks\\\\\\\"\\\\n\\\\nGOOD: \\\\\\\"Priority order: (1) Blocking issues that prevent other work, (2) User-facing bugs, (3) Performance regressions, (4) Feature work, (5) Tech debt. When two items share priority, prefer the one with more downstream dependencies.\\\\\\\"\\\\n\\\\n```\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n**4.5 Risk & Failure Anticipation**\\\\n\\\\n- Identify the 3 most likely failure modes of the prompt.\\\\n\\\\n- Embed preventive instructions or fallback behaviors.\\\\n\\\\n- For agentic prompts: define maximum iteration limits, escape hatches, and escalation triggers.\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n**4.6 Communication Protocols**\\\\n\\\\n- Define how the model should report progress, ask for clarification, a…\\\\n\\\\n\\\\ntelle me what you think about this system prompt i wrote \\\",\\\"context\\\":[],\\\"timestamp\\\":1776247747131,\\\"sessionId\\\":\\\"d7fb5344-a90f-4767-b4a8-4d839a4a99e6\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"894bea0d-0304-4615-bdf5-10cf1265b1c1\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"/​prompt-enhancer​ \\\\nimprove this prompt :\\\\nok you apply the design that I want , now improve this design. I'm not viewing my datas, my profile name anywhere on the dashboard, I'm not viewing somthing on my pages\\\",\\\"context\\\":[],\\\"timestamp\\\":1776243162990,\\\"sessionId\\\":\\\"d7fb5344-a90f-4767-b4a8-4d839a4a99e6\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"ce43aac8-e6b5-4105-898e-76748950ea24\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"/​prompt-enhancer​ ​ok you apply the design that I want , now improve this design. I'm not viewing my datas, my profile name anywhere on the dashboard, I'm not viewing somthing on my pages\\\",\\\"context\\\":[{\\\"id\\\":\\\"file:///c%3A/Users/HP/Herd/ecommerce_learn/resources/views/dashboard.blade.php\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"dashboard.blade.php\\\",\\\"value\\\":{\\\"$mid\\\":1,\\\"path\\\":\\\"/c:/Users/HP/Herd/ecommerce_learn/resources/views/dashboard.blade.php\\\",\\\"scheme\\\":\\\"file\\\"},\\\"kind\\\":\\\"file\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"file:///c%3A/Users/HP/Herd/ecommerce_learn/app/Http/Controllers/ProfileController.php\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"ProfileController.php\\\",\\\"value\\\":{\\\"$mid\\\":1,\\\"path\\\":\\\"/c:/Users/HP/Herd/ecommerce_learn/app/Http/Controllers/ProfileController.php\\\",\\\"scheme\\\":\\\"file\\\"},\\\"kind\\\":\\\"file\\\"}],\\\"timestamp\\\":1776243054017,\\\"sessionId\\\":\\\"d7fb5344-a90f-4767-b4a8-4d839a4a99e6\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"d875bd0c-5560-495b-b5a1-c8daefaad0df\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"I want ti create an app that can take any propmt and enhhance it, that's why i(m asking. if I see how your systme prompt is desogned i can surly can design better prompt for the futrure, so please teach me and create a good skill based on your systèm prompt for improving any prompt\\\",\\\"context\\\":[],\\\"timestamp\\\":1776242500336,\\\"sessionId\\\":\\\"d7fb5344-a90f-4767-b4a8-4d839a4a99e6\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"6034288c-5db4-4e6c-9ff2-474d13e16ed7\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"give me your système prompt that alllow you to enhance evry prompt i ask you to improve\\\",\\\"context\\\":[],\\\"timestamp\\\":1776242299252,\\\"sessionId\\\":\\\"d7fb5344-a90f-4767-b4a8-4d839a4a99e6\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"c76b7ebe-47c2-4537-a442-76173df07504\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Refactor the application's frontend views to strictly replicate the visual design, layout, and interactions found in the ​prototype​ folder. \\\\n\\\\nSpecific requirements:\\\\n1. **Design Fidelity**: Analyze the HTML structure and CSS variables (Morandi color palette, glassmorphism effects, spacing, typography) in ​prototype/styles/main.css​ and the corresponding HTML files (​prototype/home.html​, ​prototype/editor.html​, ​prototype/merge.html​).\\\\n2. **Tailwind CSS Migration**: Instead of using the custom CSS from the prototype, implement these styles exclusively using Tailwind CSS utility classes in the Laravel Blade views located in `resources/views/`.\\\\n3. **Configuration**: Update `tailwind.config.js` or use the `@theme` directive in `resources/css/app.css` (if using Tailwind v4 features as suggested by the project skills) to define the custom Morandi color palette (`--primary-color: #a8a29e`, `--bg-color: #F8F5F0`, etc.) so they can be used via Tailwind classes (e.g., `bg-primary`, `text-secondary`).\\\\n4. **Components**: Ensure the \\\\\\\"glass\\\\\\\" effect, rounded corners, and specific button styles from the prototype are accurately recreated using Tailwind's `backdrop-blur`, `rounded-xl`, and custom color utilities.\\\\n5. **Views to Update**: Apply this new design to `resources/views/reports/index.blade.php`, `resources/views/reports/create.blade.php` (or edit), and `resources/views/reports/merge.blade.php`.\\\\nevry page you created must be rewiriten\\\",\\\"context\\\":[{\\\"id\\\":\\\"file:///c%3A/Users/HP/Herd/ecommerce_learn/prototype_1776237009223_7j7vfktas\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"prototype\\\",\\\"value\\\":{\\\"$mid\\\":1,\\\"path\\\":\\\"/c:/Users/HP/Herd/ecommerce_learn/prototype\\\",\\\"scheme\\\":\\\"file\\\"},\\\"kind\\\":\\\"directory\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"file:///c%3A/Users/HP/Herd/ecommerce_learn/resources/views/reports/index.blade.php\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"index.blade.php\\\",\\\"value\\\":{\\\"$mid\\\":1,\\\"path\\\":\\\"/c:/Users/HP/Herd/ecommerce_learn/resources/views/reports/index.blade.php\\\",\\\"scheme\\\":\\\"file\\\"},\\\"kind\\\":\\\"file\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"file:///c%3A/Users/HP/Herd/ecommerce_learn/resources/views/reports/merge.blade.php\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"merge.blade.php\\\",\\\"value\\\":{\\\"$mid\\\":1,\\\"path\\\":\\\"/c:/Users/HP/Herd/ecommerce_learn/resources/views/reports/merge.blade.php\\\",\\\"scheme\\\":\\\"file\\\"},\\\"kind\\\":\\\"file\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"file:///c%3A/Users/HP/Herd/ecommerce_learn/resources/views/layouts/app.blade.php\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"app.blade.php\\\",\\\"value\\\":{\\\"$mid\\\":1,\\\"path\\\":\\\"/c:/Users/HP/Herd/ecommerce_learn/resources/views/layouts/app.blade.php\\\",\\\"scheme\\\":\\\"file\\\"},\\\"kind\\\":\\\"file\\\"}],\\\"timestamp\\\":1776238080156,\\\"sessionId\\\":\\\"d7fb5344-a90f-4767-b4a8-4d839a4a99e6\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"8e0ec81a-9019-4410-9f0c-48acd7cefa8e\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Please implement the missing authentication feature for the AI ReportHub application. Additionally, replace the generic default ​welcome.blade.php​ view with a proper landing page or redirect logic that aligns with the application's functionality (e.g., redirecting authenticated users to their reports dashboard).\\\",\\\"context\\\":[{\\\"id\\\":\\\"file:///c%3A/Users/HP/Herd/ecommerce_learn/resources/views/welcome.blade.php\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"welcome.blade.php\\\",\\\"value\\\":{\\\"$mid\\\":1,\\\"path\\\":\\\"/c:/Users/HP/Herd/ecommerce_learn/resources/views/welcome.blade.php\\\",\\\"scheme\\\":\\\"file\\\"},\\\"kind\\\":\\\"file\\\"},{\\\"id\\\":\\\"file:///c%3A/Users/HP/Herd/ecommerce_learn/routes/web.php\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"web.php\\\",\\\"value\\\":{\\\"$mid\\\":1,\\\"path\\\":\\\"/c:/Users/HP/Herd/ecommerce_lear